  "text": "Alternatively, there is research focusing on designing \"probabilistic circuits\" which trade accuracy for performance, power and silicon area improvements by using techniques such as voltage overscaling and imprecise architectures. For example, Palem et al. [CITATION_1] described a technique for the ripple carry adder that employed different voltage regions for different bits along a carry chain.",
